<sec>
<st>
His works</st>
<p>

Over the past 30 years, North has published a number of books of poetry, collections of poems, and an edition of critical essays.<ref xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="#xpointer(//reflist/entry[@id=%224%22])">4</ref>  His books include: <it>Six Buildings</it> (Swollen Magpie Press 1977), <it>Leap Year, Poems 1968-1978</it> (Kulchur 1978), <it>Year of the Olive Oil</it> (Hanging Loose Press 1989), <it>No Other Way: Poets, Critics, and Painters</it> (Hanging Loose Press 1998), <it>New and Selected Poems</it> (Sun and Moon Press, 1999), and <it>The Nearness of the Way You Look Tonight</it> (Adventures in Poetry 2001). North also edited <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../889/316889.xml">
anthologies</link> of <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../926/22926.xml">
poetry</link> with the late poet <physical_entity wordnetid="100001930" confidence="0.8">
